<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-437-586  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 437 586.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  May 7 1990 v11 n19 p35(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Next generation of manufacturing systems will be more responsive:Shoptalk will let shop personnel issue database queries in plainEnglish.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Coursey, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Shoptalk, an artificial intelligence (AI) software package forcomputer-integrated manufacturing (CIM) being developed at SRIInternational is described.andP;  Shoptalk will allow shop personnel topresent database queries in plain English, using words as well asthe point-and-click abilities of a mouse.andP;  Shoptalk differs frommost CIM packages in its ability to handle 'what-if' questions aswell as straight requests for data.andP;  A concept demonstrationsystem written in Prolog and running on a Unix workstation is theonly current implementation of Shoptalk.andP;  A large corporatesponsor willing to fund development of a fully functionaldemonstration system in a real factory environment is beingsought.andP;  Commercial availability could follow such a system inthree to five years.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer-Integrated ManufacturingSoftware PackagesResearch and DevelopmentNatural Language InterfacesArtificial Intelligence.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>